2026-05-03 | Sort by Count of Set Bits (Stable)

	Question
Return array sorted by set bit count.
	Approach
1.	Define function to count set bits:
		use built-in or bit manipulation  
2.	Use **stable_sort**:
		compare based on set bits  
3.	For equal set bits:
		stable_sort automatically preserves order  
	Time Complexity
	O(n log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1) (excluding sorting overhead)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int countBits(int x){
        return __builtin_popcount(x);
    }
    void sortBySetBitCount(vector<int>& arr) {
        stable_sort(arr.begin(), arr.end(),
            [&](int a, int b){
                return countBits(a) > countBits(b);
            });
    }
};
	Key Insight
- Sorting criteria: number of set bits  
- Stability requirement → use stable_sort  
This ensures:
		correct ordering + original order preserved for ties.
